e7aa1a6d-8e08-5367-b9fe-fc9782d670bd,tg:rubgr:2284,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Wedding Procession (ex. Spencer Churchill, in Musée Municipal, Brussels. A drawing in the Brit.Mus. (1935-12-14-4) after one of the men in the Wedding Procession, attrib. to Rubens (Jaffé, Master Drawings, IV, 1966, p. 134) BM Rubens exh. 1977, N° 40 reproduced. To be checked whether this attrib. is justified. Glück mentions in Large Bruegel Book 3rd.ed. in this discussion of the Wedding Procession (his N° 25) on p. 66: 'A pen drawing of certain male figures from this composition was exhibited at the 'Helsche en Fluweelen Brueghel (Tentoonstelling at P. de Boer's, A'dam 1934, N° 359'; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. The De Boer catalogue has under N° 353 Pieter Brueghel de Oude (naar) only: Figuurstudie Pentekening (as details, no illustration).'",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Wedding Procession (ex. Spencer Churchill, in Musée Municipal, Brussels. A drawing in the Brit.Mus. (1935-12-14-4) after one of the men in the Wedding Procession, attrib. to Rubens (Jaffé, Master Drawings, IV, 1966, p. 134) BM Rubens exh. 1977, N° 40 reproduced. To be checked whether this attrib. is justified. Glück mentions in Large Bruegel Book 3rd.ed. in this discussion of the Wedding Procession (his N° 25) on p. 66: 'A pen drawing of certain male figures from this composition was exhibited at the 'Helsche en Fluweelen Brueghel (Tentoonstelling at P. de Boer's, A'dam 1934, N° 359'; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. The De Boer catalogue has under N° 353 Pieter Brueghel de Oude (naar) only: Figuurstudie Pentekening (as details, no illustration).'</content>
<documentation.title>Helsche en de Fluweelen Brueghel en hun invloed op de kunst in de Nederlanden : naar aanleiding van de tentoonstelling in de kunsthandel P. De Boer</documentation.title>
